    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of evergreen perennial plant native to New Zealand and Norfolk Island. The Maori grew many varieties for specific purposes: for clothing, fishing nets, bindings, baskets, mats, and medicine.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
